# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SUOP ERP — Root Project Environment
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This is the root .env for the monorepo. It is loaded by:
#   - Next.js frontend (root app, port 3000)
#   - Prisma CLI when run from the root directory
#   - Bun runtime (auto-loads .env files walking up the directory tree)
#
# ⚠️  ENVIRONMENT LOADING ORDER (Bun + Prisma)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# When running commands from apps/backend/, Bun walks UP the tree and loads
# .env files in this order (parent → child, child wins for new keys but
# cannot unset already-set keys):
#   1. /home/z/my-project/.env              (THIS FILE — root)
#   2. /home/z/my-project/apps/backend/.env (backend dev defaults)
#
# Because Bun loads parent first, the parent's DATABASE_URL would persist
# if it were set here. THEREFORE this file MUST NOT set DATABASE_URL —
# the backend's own .env is the source of truth for the backend service.
#
# Frontend-specific env vars can live here. Backend env vars must live in
# apps/backend/.env (development), apps/backend/.env.test (test), or
# apps/backend/.env.production (production — never committed).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Next.js public env vars (exposed to browser, must be prefixed NEXT_PUBLIC_)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:3030

# Note: DATABASE_URL is intentionally NOT set here.
# See apps/backend/.env for the backend's DATABASE_URL.
